        "description": "<p><em>Star Wars: Project Porg</em> is an augmented reality game in the <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/group/70/star-wars-licensees/\">Star Wars franchise</a> which puts the player in charge of rearing a bunch of Porgs, bird-like alien pets which were introduced in the sequel trilogy of films. The Porgs appear in the player's surroundings accompanied by a device projecting a hologram of the android C-3PO (voiced by returning actor <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/person/32702/anthony-daniels/\">Anthony Daniels</a>), who advises the player on how to take care of the Porgs. The player can feed the Porgs nutrients, point a laser for them to chase after, and even pick them up and throw them, though they will always float to the ground unharmed. The player can also plant blades of grass, which, if left undisturbed, will grow into patches of grass for the Porgs to play in. The Porgs' behavior changes over time as they become more accustomed to the player, even starting to playfully mimic some of their movements.</p>",
